## Architecture — The Rendering Pipeline

### Key Files
```
d:\diacom demo\Viewers\modes\cpr\src\
  cprGpuRenderer.ts         ← GPU renderer (WebGL2, the main suspect)
  panoImageLoader.ts        ← Custom Cornerstone image loader for pano:// imageIds
  useCPROrchestrator.ts     ← Orchestrates the whole CPR flow (3200+ lines)

d:\diacom demo\Viewers\extensions\cornerstone\src\services\ViewportService\
  CornerstoneViewportService.ts  ← OHIF's viewport management, calls setStack
```

### The Rendering Flow

```
useCPROrchestrator.ts
  → calls cprGpuRenderer.renderPanoGpu(...)
      → uploads volume to R32F WebGL2 3D texture
      → renders curved plane via fragment shader
      → readPixels → Float32Array (the "pixelData")
      → returns { pixelData, width, height, minValue, maxValue }
  → calls setPanoImagePayload(panoImageId, { pixelData, windowWidth, windowCenter, ... })
      → stores payload in panoImageLoader.ts memory cache
  → calls panoViewport.setStack(['pano://current/...'], 0)
      → Cornerstone calls panoImageLoader to resolve the imageId
      → panoImageLoader returns a Cornerstone IImage object with getPixelData()
      → Cornerstone uploads pixelData to GPU for display
      → Cornerstone applies VOI (voiRange) to transfer function → renders to canvas
```

